Program: Discovery
Title: Measuring time
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxkl
Last Broadcast Date: 21 December 1999
A look at time; how we measure minutes, weeks, months and years. The first calenders date back to the Stone Age, and man has long been obsessed with making sure he can keep track of time. The earth's orbit of the Sun is not exactly 365 days, so a calender was made to introduce a leap day every four years, but even that isn't exact. Show less